cs.ET, cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.QUANT, cs.SE 

The paper discusses the use of quantum process calculus to model and verify linear optical quantum computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.ET (Emerging Technologies), which includes papers on new and emerging technologies in computer science. The paper also involves process calculus, which suggests the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). The use of Fock states and number states to describe photons indicates the sub-category cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also deals with quantum computing, which falls under the sub-category cs.QUANT (Quantum Physics). Finally, the paper involves verification of models, which suggests the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering).
